8  |  DISCOVERY QUESTIONS — Surface DNV ShipManager weaknesses naturally

Ask without naming DNV ShipManager. Expose gaps that favour AMOS™.

•	If your asset management system were sold by the same organisation that surveys your vessels — how comfortable are you with that relationship? Who is the software optimised for?
•	Does your fleet management software hold approvals from all the class societies your vessels are surveyed under — and would a class change or fleet acquisition create a compliance gap?
•	When your maintenance system, your emissions reporting, and your compliance benchmarking are all on the same vendor's platform — how do you ensure data independence and commercial objectivity?
•	Is the platform purpose-built for maritime asset management, or is it one product within a broader multi-industry conglomerate that also sells software for wind turbines, pipelines, and healthcare?
•	When you need multi-entity governance reporting across regions at board level — have you seen that demonstrated at your fleet's complexity level?
•	What is your current three-way invoice match rate — and what does a failed match cost in investigation time per incident?
•	How much procurement spend variance do you carry per quarter — and can you see it in real time at the point of requisition approval?
•	Can you speak to a reference customer who has been live on the platform for 5+ years at a similar fleet size and safety-critical complexity to yours?

